From: Vincent Fortier <th0ma7@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 01 Jun 2026
Subject: [PATCH] profile: don't gate sharer packet drop on PCR (fixes lost MP4 audio)

When a subscription joins an already-running shared transcoder (e.g. a rapid
same-channel profile switch mkv->mp4), profile_sharer_deliver() rebases its
timestamps against prch_ts_delta (computed from the first packet seen, typically
video) and drops any packet whose pts/dts/pcr is below that delta.

Transcoded AAC packets carry a pkt_pcr that trails their pts/dts by several
seconds. Their pts/dts are above the delta (current content), but their pcr is
far below it, so the pcr clause of the gate dropped EVERY audio packet. With no
audio packets arriving, globalheaders disabled the audio component after its
MAX_NOPKT_TIME (7.5s) timeout, and the MP4 muxer built a video-only track:
audio was missing until the user re-selected the channel (which spawns a fresh,
non-shared transcoder where prch_ts_delta is 0 and no correction applies).

Confirmed with LS_PROFILE trace: hundreds of
  "packet drop (delta 861680) (pkt stream 2 AAC-LATM pcr 464896 dts 871680 ...)"
i.e. dts/pts >= delta but pcr << delta.

Fix: gate the drop on pts/dts only (the actual "is this packet current?" test)
and clamp the rebased pcr so it never underflows. Genuinely pre-join packets
still drop on the dts/pts test; only audio with a lagging pcr is now kept.

Suggested-by: Claude Opus 4.8 (Anthropic AI <https://anthropic.com>)
Signed-off-by: Vincent Fortier <th0ma7@gmail.com>

--- src/profile.c.orig	2026-05-19 20:37:17.000000000 +0000
+++ src/profile.c	2026-06-01 09:00:00.000000000 +0000
@@ -779,13 +779,18 @@
      * time correction here
      */
     if (pkt->pkt_pts >= prch->prch_ts_delta &&
-        pkt->pkt_dts >= prch->prch_ts_delta &&
-        pkt->pkt_pcr >= prch->prch_ts_delta) {
+        pkt->pkt_dts >= prch->prch_ts_delta) {
       th_pkt_t *n = pkt_copy_shallow(pkt);
       pkt_ref_dec(pkt);
       n->pkt_pts -= prch->prch_ts_delta;
       n->pkt_dts -= prch->prch_ts_delta;
-      n->pkt_pcr -= prch->prch_ts_delta;
+      // pkt_pcr can legitimately lag pts/dts (notably for transcoded audio, whose
+      // pcr trails its dts by several seconds). Gating the drop on pcr discarded
+      // the whole audio track on a late sharer join (rapid same-channel profile
+      // switch), so globalheaders timed out and disabled audio -> MP4 video-only.
+      // Gate only on pts/dts; clamp the rebased pcr so it never underflows.
+      n->pkt_pcr = (pkt->pkt_pcr >= prch->prch_ts_delta) ?
+                     pkt->pkt_pcr - prch->prch_ts_delta : 0;
       sm->sm_data = n;
     } else {
       pkt_trace(LS_PROFILE, pkt, "packet drop (delta %"PRId64")", prch->prch_ts_delta);
